qas.question: What treaty was supposed to stop Germany from having antiaircraft weapons?
When did covert antiaircraft training start in Germany?
When did the 10.5 centimeter FlaK 38 appear in Germany?
When did the design begin for the 12.8 centimeter FlaK?

context: The <a0_0>Treaty of Versailles<a0_0/> prevented Germany having AA weapons, and for example, the Krupps designers joined Bofors in Sweden. Some World War I guns were retained and some covert AA training started <a1_0>in the late 1920s<a1_0/>. Germany introduced the 8.8 cm FlaK 18 in 1933, 36 and 37 models followed with various improvements but ballistic performance was unchanged. <a2_0>In the late 1930s<a2_0/> the 10.5 cm FlaK 38 appeared soon followed by the 39, this was designed primarily for static sites but had a mobile mounting and the unit had <a4_0>220v 24 kW generators<a4_0/>.
